The paper deals with the Online Metric Matching problem, which is a classic problem in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves optimizing the matching of clients to servers, which can be modeled as a game-theoretic problem (cs.GT). The paper proposes new algorithms for this problem, which involve analyzing and optimizing the performance of these algorithms (cs.LG). The algorithms also involve making decisions based on the data available, which can be seen as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of these algorithms in terms of information theory, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
